issue_comment_body:
Using `NoEscape` with the `\label{}` inside the `\caption{}` does indeed work.  (Is there a way to put a `\label{}` into the pylatex figure object other than in the caption?)  The only remaining problem is running latex multiple times to get the cross references correct.

The code below generates the correct latex output.

    image_filename = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), 'kitten.jpg')

    geometry_options = {"tmargin": "1cm", "lmargin": "10cm"}
    doc = Document(geometry_options=geometry_options)

    with doc.create(Section('Some Section')):
        doc.append('Here is some text.')
        doc.append(NoEscape(r'Hey, look at Figure \ref{fig:kitten}.'))

        with doc.create(Figure(position='h!')) as kitten_pic:
            kitten_pic.add_image(image_filename, width='120px')
            kitten_pic.add_caption(NoEscape(r'\label{fig:kitten} This is a figure.'))

    doc.generate_tex('full', clean_tex=False)

This call to `generate_tex()` results in the correct latex below:

    \documentclass{article}
    \usepackage[T1]{fontenc}
    \usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
    \usepackage{lmodern}
    \usepackage{graphicx}

    \begin{document}
    \section{Some Section}
    Here is some text.
    Hey, look at Figure \ref{fig:kitten}.

    \begin{figure}[h!]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=120px]{examples/pylatex/kitten.jpg}
    \caption{\label{fig:kitten} This is a figure.}
    \end{figure}

    \end{document}


and then running a few iterations of `pdflatex` _from the command line_, I get a pdf with correctly numbered references to figures like this:

![goodlatex](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2047822/20954204/30c5aff4-bc07-11e6-985e-cf484f2ca234.png)

:exclamation: However, it's not clear to me how to get pylatex to iterate processing to get cross references correct.  Using `generate_pdf()` does not get the cross-references right.  Is there a way to get the cross references correct using pure pylatex (no system calls to `pdflatex`)?

