I should have said that Subscription.renew() in the existing version of events.py doesn't seem to be thread safe, despite the warning about thread safety, because it reads and changes variables of the Subscription object without a lock. Not being proficient with threads, I haven't yet attempted to address this. 

The problem doesn't arise in the same way in the twisted version, because it doesn't use threads. However, a version of the same issue could arise, because calls to the new SubscriptionBase.request function aren't queued. For example, a request could be made first to SUBSCRIBE, then UNSUBSCRIBE a service. In theory, the Sonos device could respond to the UNSUBSCRIBE request first. I've no idea whether this could happen in practice.

