The problem is that this will handle only one exception. More to say, in your code there is two logger callers for same exception: [here](https://github.com/aio-libs/aioftp/pull/62/files#diff-df09d65446d1f455524ad37a0e1107c5R892) and [here](https://github.com/aio-libs/aioftp/pull/62/files#diff-df09d65446d1f455524ad37a0e1107c5R917)

I think it is better to make logging decorator:
``` python
def log_exception_and_return(*, message, logger=None):

    def decorator(coro):

        @functools.wraps(coro)
        async def wrapper(*args,  **kwargs):
            try:
                return await coro(*args, **kwargs)
            except asyncio.CancelledError:
                raise
            except:  # noqa
                if logger is not None:
                    logger.exception(message)

        return wrapper
        
    return decorator


@log_exception_and_return(message="dispatcher caught exception", logger=logger)
async def dispatcher(self, reader, writer):
    ...    
    try:
        while True:
            done, pending = ...
            for task in done:
                try:
                    result = task.result()                    
                except errors.PathIOError:
                    connection.response("451", "file system error")
                    continue
    ...
```

